<body>

<div class="page">

  <div class="mockup-banner">
    <strong>Layout mockup v2 for review.</strong> Not live. Updated per your notes:<br>
    1. Intro paragraph reworded so it stands alone (no "one rule that binds them" reference).
    2. Commissioner block now matches Supplier block styling — dark blue, white text, amber border.
    3. Three strategic questions lifted to sit between the contextual blocks and Direction of Travel.
    4. Swooping arrows now cascade through every level: cards → contextual blocks → strategic questions → Direction of Travel.
  </div>

  <div class="amber-rule"></div>
  <div class="h-eyebrow">The reason this exists &middot; mockup view</div>
  <h1 class="h-title">Why.</h1>
  <p class="h-sub">Hero text continues as it is on the live page. The mockup focuses on the spine, the contextual blocks, the strategic questions and the destination.</p>

  <!-- ============ SPINE SECTION ============ -->
  <div style="background:linear-gradient(135deg,#003087,#005EB8);color:#fff;border-radius:18px;padding:34px 38px;margin:36px 0 0;box-shadow:0 14px 40px rgba(0,48,135,0.20);position:relative;">
    <div style="font-size:11px;font-weight:800;letter-spacing:2px;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.78);text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:10px;">The spine of the model</div>
    <h2 style="font-size:32px;font-weight:900;color:#fff;letter-spacing:-0.7px;line-height:1.1;margin-bottom:14px;">Orchestrate the market. Do not supply it.</h2>
    <p style="font-size:15.5px;line-height:1.65;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.95);max-width:880px;margin-bottom:18px;">NHSE is the matchmaker, the market-maker, the bridge between innovation and care. It sets the standards, manages the framework, builds the integrations and runs the platform. It does not sign local contracts, own the billing, deliver care, or pick a single supplier. Anything that pulls NHSE into being the supplier breaks the 2030 vision.</p>

    <div style="background:rgba(255,255,255,0.14);border:1.5px solid #FFB91D;border-radius:14px;padding:22px 26px;margin-top:14px;">
      <div style="font-size:10.5px;font-weight:800;letter-spacing:1.8px;color:#FFD66B;text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:12px;">North Star &middot; the purpose every actor serves</div>
      <div style="display:flex;gap:14px;align-items:flex-start;flex-wrap:wrap;">
        <div style="display:flex;flex-shrink:0;">
          <img src="Assets/Personas/abdul.png" alt="Abdul" style="width:50px;height:50px;border-radius:50%;border:2.5px solid #FFB91D;object-fit:cover;object-position:top center;background:#fff;">
          <img src="Assets/Personas/mark.png" alt="Mark" style="width:50px;height:50px;border-radius:50%;border:2.5px solid #FFB91D;object-fit:cover;object-position:top center;background:#fff;margin-left:-12px;">
          <img src="Assets/Personas/layla.png" alt="Layla" style="width:50px;height:50px;border-radius:50%;border:2.5px solid #FFB91D;object-fit:cover;object-position:top center;background:#fff;margin-left:-12px;">
          <img src="Assets/Personas/sean.png" alt="Sean" style="width:50px;height:50px;border-radius:50%;border:2.5px solid #FFB91D;object-fit:cover;object-position:top center;background:#fff;margin-left:-12px;">
        </div>
        <div style="flex:1;min-width:280px;">
          <div style="font-size:23px;font-weight:900;color:#fff;line-height:1.18;margin-bottom:9px;letter-spacing:-0.4px;">Better outcomes, reached fairly.</div>
          <div style="font-size:13.5px;line-height:1.6;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.92);">Above every actor&apos;s north star sits one shared end: <strong style="color:#fff;">better access</strong> for the people a clinic-based system leaves behind, <strong style="color:#fff;">earlier detection</strong> at population scale, and <strong style="color:#fff;">fairer outcomes</strong> by closing the gap in who gets tested and when.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- NEW INTRO PARAGRAPH (reworded — no longer references "one rule that binds them") -->
    <div style="background:rgba(255,255,255,0.08);border-left:4px solid #FFD66B;border-radius:0 12px 12px 0;padding:18px 22px;margin:24px 0 18px;">
      <div style="font-size:10.5px;font-weight:800;letter-spacing:1.8px;color:#FFD66B;text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:8px;">Four actors. Four north stars. All four have to hold at once.</div>
      <div style="font-size:15px;line-height:1.65;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.95);">The supplier makes money. The commissioner saves money or gets more for the same money. The clinician&apos;s time goes where it is needed. The centre is funded through orchestration, never as the supplier. These are simultaneous conditions, not trade-offs &mdash; <strong style="color:#fff;">if any one of them fails, the platform fails</strong>, and the patient purpose at the top goes unmet.</div>
    </div>

    <!-- FOUR ACTOR CARDS — Commissioner | Centre | Clinician | Supplier -->
    <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(4,1fr);gap:14px;">
      <div style="background:rgba(255,255,255,0.10);border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.22);border-radius:12px;padding:18px 20px;">
        <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:10px;margin-bottom:10px;"><img src="Assets/Personas/sarah.png" alt="Sarah" style="width:38px;height:38px;border-radius:50%;border:2px solid #FFD66B;object-fit:cover;object-position:top center;background:#fff;flex-shrink:0;"><div style="font-size:10px;font-weight:800;letter-spacing:1.6px;color:#FFD66B;text-transform:uppercase;">Commissioner</div></div>
        <div style="font-size:17px;font-weight:800;color:#fff;line-height:1.25;margin-bottom:8px;">Easy buying.</div>
        <div style="font-size:11.5px;line-height:1.5;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.88);margin-bottom:7px;">Ready-made, not bespoke: find it, decide it&apos;s right, onboard, go live.</div>
        <div style="font-size:11px;line-height:1.5;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.78);border-top:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.18);padding-top:7px;"><strong style="color:#fff;">The money:</strong> saves, or gets more for the same money, at pathway level.</div>
      </div>
      <div style="background:rgba(255,255,255,0.10);border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.22);border-radius:12px;padding:18px 20px;">
        <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:10px;margin-bottom:10px;"><img src="Assets/Personas/priya.png" alt="Priya" style="width:38px;height:38px;border-radius:50%;border:2px solid #7EC8E3;object-fit:cover;object-position:top center;background:#fff;flex-shrink:0;"><div style="font-size:10px;font-weight:800;letter-spacing:1.6px;color:#7EC8E3;text-transform:uppercase;">The centre</div></div>
        <div style="font-size:17px;font-weight:800;color:#fff;line-height:1.25;margin-bottom:8px;">Matchmaker, not counterparty.</div>
        <div style="font-size:11.5px;line-height:1.5;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.88);margin-bottom:7px;">Set the standards, run the platform, hold the 2030 vision. Never the supplier.</div>
        <div style="font-size:11px;line-height:1.5;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.78);border-top:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.18);padding-top:7px;"><strong style="color:#fff;">The money:</strong> funded sustainably through orchestration, not through supply.</div>
      </div>
      <div style="background:rgba(255,255,255,0.10);border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.22);border-radius:12px;padding:18px 20px;">
        <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:10px;margin-bottom:10px;"><img src="Assets/Personas/aisha.png" alt="Aisha" style="width:38px;height:38px;border-radius:50%;border:2px solid #C9A0E3;object-fit:cover;object-position:top center;background:#fff;flex-shrink:0;"><div style="font-size:10px;font-weight:800;letter-spacing:1.6px;color:#C9A0E3;text-transform:uppercase;">Clinician</div></div>
        <div style="font-size:17px;font-weight:800;color:#fff;line-height:1.25;margin-bottom:8px;">Pathway fit.</div>
        <div style="font-size:11.5px;line-height:1.5;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.88);margin-bottom:7px;">The test arrives inside the pathway I already run, not as a second screen.</div>
        <div style="font-size:11px;line-height:1.5;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.78);border-top:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.18);padding-top:7px;"><strong style="color:#fff;">The value:</strong> clinic time concentrates where it is needed; routine work leaves the room.</div>
      </div>
      <div style="background:rgba(255,255,255,0.10);border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.22);border-radius:12px;padding:18px 20px;">
        <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:10px;margin-bottom:10px;"><img src="Assets/Personas/joe.png" alt="Joe" style="width:38px;height:38px;border-radius:50%;border:2px solid #5BC093;object-fit:cover;object-position:top center;background:#fff;flex-shrink:0;"><div style="font-size:10px;font-weight:800;letter-spacing:1.6px;color:#5BC093;text-transform:uppercase;">Supplier</div></div>
        <div style="font-size:17px;font-weight:800;color:#fff;line-height:1.25;margin-bottom:8px;">Easy onboarding.</div>
        <div style="font-size:11.5px;line-height:1.5;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.88);margin-bottom:7px;">A clean, repeatable route to volume: onboard once, reuse across conditions.</div>
        <div style="font-size:11px;line-height:1.5;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.78);border-top:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.18);padding-top:7px;"><strong style="color:#fff;">The money:</strong> sell across conditions with no assurance burden per deployment.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ARROW ROW 1: cards → contextual blocks -->
  <div style="position:relative;height:60px;margin:-4px 0;">
    <svg viewBox="0 0 1020 60" preserveAspectRatio="none" style="width:100%;height:100%;display:block;overflow:visible;">
      <path d="M 130 0 C 130 32, 250 26, 250 56" stroke="#FFD66B" stroke-width="3" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-dasharray="6 4"/>
      <polygon points="250,60 244,52 256,52" fill="#FFD66B"/>
      <path d="M 890 0 C 890 32, 770 26, 770 56" stroke="#FFD66B" stroke-width="3" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-dasharray="6 4"/>
      <polygon points="770,60 764,52 776,52" fill="#FFD66B"/>
    </svg>
  </div>

  <!-- TWO HALF-WIDTH CONTEXTUAL BLOCKS (both now dark blue with white text) -->
  <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:18px;">
    <!-- LEFT: pathway econ — matches supplier styling -->
    <div style="background:linear-gradient(135deg,#003087,#005EB8);border:2px solid #FFB91D;border-radius:12px;padding:22px 24px;color:#fff;">
      <div style="font-size:10.5px;font-weight:800;letter-spacing:1.8px;color:#FFD66B;text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:8px;">For the commissioner &middot; where the economics actually resolves</div>
      <h3 style="font-size:22px;font-weight:900;color:#fff;letter-spacing:-0.4px;line-height:1.18;margin-bottom:10px;">The commissioner case lands at pathway level.</h3>
      <p style="font-size:13px;line-height:1.62;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.92);margin:0 0 8px;">The economics lens above is necessary, not sufficient. In live commissioning, the cost of a new test and the saving it produces sit on different budget lines.</p>
      <p style="font-size:13px;line-height:1.62;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.92);margin:0;">The model only delivers at scale when the test sits inside a pathway and the pathway carries the economics. <strong style="color:#fff;">Configurations only land where the commissioner has a viable funding route at the pathway level.</strong></p>
    </div>
    <!-- RIGHT: supplier onboarding -->
    <div style="background:linear-gradient(135deg,#003087,#005EB8);border:2px solid #FFB91D;border-radius:12px;padding:22px 24px;color:#fff;">
      <div style="font-size:10.5px;font-weight:800;letter-spacing:1.8px;color:#FFD66B;text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:8px;">For the supplier &middot; the structural commitment</div>
      <h3 style="font-size:22px;font-weight:900;color:#fff;letter-spacing:-0.4px;line-height:1.18;margin-bottom:10px;">Assure once. Reuse nationally.</h3>
      <p style="font-size:13px;line-height:1.62;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.92);margin:0;">A supplier admitted to the framework is admitted once. The clinical safety case, the IG package and the lab assurance are then portable across every commissioner who calls them off. The local body acts as the deployment authority, not as a re-assurer. The centre&apos;s job is the upstream assurance; the local job is administering the deployment, not redoing the work.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ARROW ROW 2: contextual blocks → strategic questions -->
  <div style="position:relative;height:60px;margin:-4px 0;">
    <svg viewBox="0 0 1020 60" preserveAspectRatio="none" style="width:100%;height:100%;display:block;overflow:visible;">
      <!-- Left arrow: from centre of left block (~255px) down to a left-ish point in strategic questions row -->
      <path d="M 255 0 C 255 28, 340 28, 340 56" stroke="#FFD66B" stroke-width="3" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-dasharray="6 4"/>
      <polygon points="340,60 334,52 346,52" fill="#FFD66B"/>
      <!-- Right arrow: from centre of right block (~765px) down to a right-ish point in strategic questions row -->
      <path d="M 765 0 C 765 28, 680 28, 680 56" stroke="#FFD66B" stroke-width="3" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-dasharray="6 4"/>
      <polygon points="680,60 674,52 686,52" fill="#FFD66B"/>
    </svg>
  </div>

  <!-- THREE STRATEGIC QUESTIONS (lifted from the bottom of the page) -->
  <div style="background:#F4F8FC;border:1px solid #D5E8F0;border-radius:14px;padding:26px 30px;">
    <div style="font-size:11px;font-weight:800;letter-spacing:1.8px;color:#005EB8;text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:8px;">What we&apos;re trying to figure out at a strategic level</div>
    <h2 style="font-size:24px;font-weight:800;color:#003087;letter-spacing:-0.4px;line-height:1.2;margin-bottom:8px;">Three strategic questions.</h2>
    <p style="font-size:13.5px;line-height:1.65;color:#4C6272;margin-bottom:18px;max-width:820px;">Cross-cutting questions that <strong>apply to every product</strong>, not just one stage or one pathway. The four north stars frame why the model exists. These three frame what is genuinely hard about making it work.</p>
    <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr);gap:14px;">
      <div style="background:#fff;border:1px solid #d6e2ef;border-top:4px solid #005EB8;border-radius:10px;padding:18px 20px;">
        <div style="font-size:10.5px;font-weight:800;letter-spacing:1.6px;color:#7E8B97;text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:8px;">Question 01</div>
        <div style="font-size:15px;font-weight:800;color:#003087;letter-spacing:-0.2px;line-height:1.3;margin-bottom:8px;">Route to market.</div>
        <div style="font-size:12.5px;line-height:1.6;color:#4C6272;">What is the best route to market? How does the centre create a market for each product so that demand and supply meet in a way that scales?</div>
      </div>
      <div style="background:#fff;border:1px solid #d6e2ef;border-top:4px solid #005EB8;border-radius:10px;padding:18px 20px;">
        <div style="font-size:10.5px;font-weight:800;letter-spacing:1.6px;color:#7E8B97;text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:8px;">Question 02</div>
        <div style="font-size:15px;font-weight:800;color:#003087;letter-spacing:-0.2px;line-height:1.3;margin-bottom:8px;">Commercial viability.</div>
        <div style="font-size:12.5px;line-height:1.6;color:#4C6272;">How is this made attractive to commissioners, financially viable for suppliers, and demonstrably value for money for the NHS, all at the same time?</div>
      </div>
      <div style="background:#fff;border:1px solid #d6e2ef;border-top:4px solid #005EB8;border-radius:10px;padding:18px 20px;">
        <div style="font-size:10.5px;font-weight:800;letter-spacing:1.6px;color:#7E8B97;text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:8px;">Question 03</div>
        <div style="font-size:15px;font-weight:800;color:#003087;letter-spacing:-0.2px;line-height:1.3;margin-bottom:8px;">Supply chain at scale.</div>
        <div style="font-size:12.5px;line-height:1.6;color:#4C6272;">How is a supply chain built that can handle different use cases, different initiation patterns, and grow with volume without fragmenting?</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ARROW ROW 3: strategic questions → Direction of Travel -->
  <div style="position:relative;height:60px;margin:-4px 0;">
    <svg viewBox="0 0 1020 60" preserveAspectRatio="none" style="width:100%;height:100%;display:block;overflow:visible;">
      <!-- Two arrows converging toward Direction of Travel headline -->
      <path d="M 340 0 C 340 28, 430 28, 430 56" stroke="#FFD66B" stroke-width="3" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-dasharray="6 4"/>
      <polygon points="430,60 424,52 436,52" fill="#FFD66B"/>
      <path d="M 680 0 C 680 28, 590 28, 590 56" stroke="#FFD66B" stroke-width="3" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-dasharray="6 4"/>
      <polygon points="590,60 584,52 596,52" fill="#FFD66B"/>
    </svg>
  </div>

  <!-- DIRECTION OF TRAVEL -->
  <div style="background:linear-gradient(135deg,#003087,#005EB8);border-radius:18px;padding:34px 38px;color:#fff;box-shadow:0 14px 40px rgba(0,48,135,0.20);">
    <div style="font-size:11px;font-weight:800;letter-spacing:2px;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.78);text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:10px;">Direction of travel</div>
    <h2 style="font-size:32px;font-weight:900;color:#fff;letter-spacing:-0.7px;line-height:1.1;margin-bottom:14px;">From launch to self-sustaining.</h2>
    <p style="font-size:15.5px;line-height:1.65;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.95);max-width:880px;margin-bottom:24px;">The orchestrator stance holds throughout. What changes between launch and 2030 is how the operating envelope is funded, not who is the buyer. Three time bands, one direction.</p>
    <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr);gap:14px;">
      <div style="background:rgba(255,255,255,0.10);border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.22);border-radius:12px;padding:20px 22px;">
        <div style="font-size:10.5px;font-weight:800;letter-spacing:1.6px;color:#FFD66B;text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:10px;">Day 1 &middot; launch through 2026/27</div>
        <div style="font-size:17px;font-weight:900;color:#fff;line-height:1.22;margin-bottom:10px;letter-spacing:-0.3px;">Commissioner-to-supplier direct.</div>
        <div style="font-size:13px;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.92);line-height:1.6;">Commissioners hold the budget and pay suppliers directly. NHSE runs the framework, the standards and the platform.</div>
      </div>
      <div style="background:rgba(255,255,255,0.10);border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.22);border-radius:12px;padding:20px 22px;">
        <div style="font-size:10.5px;font-weight:800;letter-spacing:1.6px;color:#FFD66B;text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:10px;">Year 2/3 &middot; transition begins</div>
        <div style="font-size:17px;font-weight:900;color:#fff;line-height:1.22;margin-bottom:10px;letter-spacing:-0.3px;">The platform-fee model lands.</div>
        <div style="font-size:13px;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.92);line-height:1.6;">Suppliers admitted to the framework pay a Procurement Act compliant management fee on call-off only.</div>
      </div>
      <div style="background:rgba(255,255,255,0.10);border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.22);border-radius:12px;padding:20px 22px;">
        <div style="font-size:10.5px;font-weight:800;letter-spacing:1.6px;color:#FFD66B;text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:10px;">2030 &middot; destination</div>
        <div style="font-size:17px;font-weight:900;color:#fff;line-height:1.22;margin-bottom:10px;letter-spacing:-0.3px;">Self-sustaining.</div>
        <div style="font-size:13px;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.92);line-height:1.6;">HomeTest pays for itself. The framework fee plus accountable savings credited to the system cover the operating envelope.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div style="margin-top:36px;padding:18px 22px;background:#F4F8FC;border:1px dashed #B5D4E5;border-radius:10px;font-size:12.5px;color:#4C6272;line-height:1.6;">
    <strong>Sections below remain in the same order as the current page:</strong> Venn (Three actors. One platform around them.) &middot; Precedent (Same shape as existing NHS national models). Strategic questions has moved up &mdash; it now sits between the contextual blocks and Direction of Travel.
  </div>

</div>

</body>
</html>
